ğŸ”§ Code Structure

Major Improvements from v1.0

1. Object-Oriented Design

    Before: Linear procedural code with recursive function calls

    After: CSECCalculator class with proper state management

    Benefit: Better modularity and maintainability

2. Enhanced Error Handling

    Before: Basic try-catch with recursion on errors

    After: Comprehensive exception handling with user-friendly messages

    Benefit: Graceful error recovery without program termination

3. Input Validation System

    Before: Limited number validation

    After: Advanced input parsing with special keyword support

    Benefit: More intuitive user experience

Key Components

    CSECCalculator - Main calculator class

    basic_operations() - Handles arithmetic operations

    scientific_operations() - Advanced mathematical functions

    financial_operations() - Financial calculations

    complex_operations() - Complex number arithmetic

    memory_operations() - Memory management

    statistics_operations() - Statistical analysis

ğŸ›¡ï¸ Safety & Reliability
Input Security

    Validated float conversion with special keyword support

    Prevents crashes and invalid operations

Division Safety

    Explicit zero-division prevention with clear error messages

Memory Management

    Automatic save/load with size limits (100 entries)

    Data persistence between sessions

